<HEADLINE>
FT  18 JUN 92 / Parliament and Politics: Labour Euro committee chairman
unseated
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
MR Nigel Spearing, Labour MP for Newham South, was yesterday voted out of
the key post of chairman of the all-party select committee on European
legislation, though he remains a member.
The committee, which sifts EC legislation and recommends the most important
measures for debate either in committee or in the Commons itself, is a key
part of Westminster's mechanism for scrutinising proposals from Brussels. Mr
Spearing, who has held the post since 1983, was defeated by Mr Jimmy Hood,
Labour MP for Clydesdale.
</TEXT>
