<HEADLINE>
FT  17 JUN 92 / World Commodities Prices: Cotton and Jute
</HEADLINE>
<DATELINE>
   COTTON Liverpool
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Spot and shipment sales for the week ended 12 June 1992 amounted to 126
tonnes against 437 tonees in the previous week. Sales were low and occured
mainly in West African, Central Asian and Israeli growths.
JUTE June/July: C and F Dundee: BTC Dollars 405, BWC n/o, BTD Dollars 370,
BWD n/o: C and F Antwerp BTC Dollars 380, BWC Dollars 380, BTD Dollars 355,
BWD Dollars 355.
</TEXT>
<PUB>The Financial Times
